{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 \line
### Borg Backup Management\line
\line
Borg is a deduplicating backup program that supports compression and encryption, designed for efficient local backups with fast recovery.\line
\line
Key features:\line
- Powerful deduplication (saves space by storing identical data only once)\line
- Multiple compression options\line
- Strong encryption\line
- Efficient incremental backups\line
- Flexible retention policies\line
- Repository consistency checking\line
\line
Configuration:\line
```bash\line
# ~/.borg-env\line
export BORG_REPO="/path/to/repo"\line
export BORG_PASSPHRASE="your-secure-passphrase"\line
export RETENTION_DAYS=7\line
export RETENTION_WEEKS=4\line
export RETENTION_MONTHS=6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Implementation:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 #!/bin/bash\line
source ~/.borg-env\line
\line
# Create unique archive name\line
ARCHIVE_NAME="backup-$(date +%Y-%m-%d-%H%M)"\line
\line
# Create backup\line
borg create \\\line
    --compression zlib,9 \\\line
    --exclude '*.DS_Store' \\\line
    --exclude '*/tmp/*' \\\line
    --exclude '**/__pycache__/*' \\\line
    "$BORG_REPO::$ARCHIVE_NAME" $HOME/Documents $HOME/Projects\line
\line
# Prune old backups\line
borg prune \\\line
    --keep-daily=$RETENTION_DAYS \\\line
    --keep-weekly=$RETENTION_WEEKS \\\line
    --keep-monthly=$RETENTION_MONTHS \\\line
    "$BORG_REPO"\par}
